author: seattlepi.com
title: Rocky Mountain National Park superintendent retires
text:
ROCKY MOUNTAIN NATIONAL PARK, Colo. (AP) â€” Rocky Mountain National Park Superintendent Vaughn Baker has retired after 42 years of public service.
Park officials said Friday that Baker retired earlier in the week and plans to stay in nearby Estes Park. During his 13 years at Rocky Mountain National Park, he led staff through numerous high-profile fires, dealt with a massive beetle outbreak and managed the response to devastating floods in 2013.
The Billings, Montana native began his career with the National Park Service in 1984. Before that, he worked for the Bureau of Land Management .
Ben Bobowski , Chief of Resource Stewardship at Rocky Mountain National Park, will be acting superintendent until the post is filled.
